body:
Within a certain range yes, all Marksmen (and women) tend to be the &quot;deal lots of sustained damage&quot; class

But IMO there are regardless 3 distinct Marksman sub-classes that should be recognized, I don&#039;t have names for them, I&#039;m just going to talk about what they do.

&quot;Raw Damage&quot;

This is what Rito was talking about; get into range and blast people with TONS OF DAMAGE, but you don&#039;t do much else. **This is Kog&#039;maw, Vayne, Miss Fortune, Tristana, Corki, Twitch, Lucian, Graves**.

&quot;Snipers&quot;

These guys and girls break the range-boundary and have an impact on fights from further away than any other marksman, typically with a huge burst of damage (NOT sustained, not doing &quot;the same thing but different&quot; here). This is **Jinx, Jhin, Caitlyn, Draven, Ezreal**.

&quot;Play-makers&quot;

Here we have Marksman that feature big, game-changing, momentous abilities and play-making potential outside of just dealing damage. They may also offer strong utility in other ways. This is **Ashe, Sivir, Quinn, Varus, Kalista, Kindred, Urgot, Teemo** (still a marksman folks)

There are even a few cross-class Hybrids like Quinn (brings raw damage with game-changing roam potential), Varus (Pokes at fairly long range but also brings that nice Ulti to team-fights), and Ashe (delivers big stuns from anywhere on the map).

EDIT: Just my personal name suggestions in the order above; **Hunters** (or **Bounty Hunters**), keep **Snipers**, **Rangers**
